    <item>
      <title>How to Fix Content Security Policy Web Worker Errors</title>
      <link>https://www.sitebay.org/docs/guides/fix-content-security-policy-web-worker-error/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 16 Mar 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://www.sitebay.org/docs/guides/fix-content-security-policy-web-worker-error/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;How to Fix Content Security Policy Web Worker Errors&#xA;Encountering the error:&#xA;Refused to create a worker from &amp;lsquo;blob:&amp;hellip;&amp;rsquo; because it violates the following Content Security Policy directive: &amp;ldquo;script-src &amp;lsquo;self&amp;rsquo; &amp;hellip;&amp;rdquo;. Note that &amp;lsquo;worker-src&amp;rsquo; was not explicitly set, so &amp;lsquo;script-src&amp;rsquo; is used as a fallback.&#xA;can be frustrating, especially when implementing Web Workers or similar features that rely on blob or data URLs. This article explains why this error occurs and provides a clear solution to quickly fix it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
